# Keystatic GitHub Mode Configuration
# Documentation: https://keystatic.com/docs/github-mode

# GitHub OAuth App credentials
KEYSTATIC_GITHUB_CLIENT_ID=your_github_oauth_app_client_id
KEYSTATIC_GITHUB_CLIENT_SECRET=your_github_oauth_app_client_secret

# Keystatic secret for signing session cookies
# Generate with: node scripts/generate-keystatic-secret.js
KEYSTATIC_SECRET=your_generated_secret_here

# CRITICAL: Keystatic uses these exact environment variable names
# Do NOT rename them or use GITHUB_CLIENT_ID/GITHUB_CLIENT_SECRET

# Instructions:
# 1. Create a GitHub OAuth App at https://github.com/settings/developers
#    - Click "New OAuth App"
#    - Application name: "Your Site Name Keystatic"
#
# 2. Configure the OAuth app URLs:
#    - Homepage URL: https://your-domain.vercel.app
#    - Authorization callback URL: https://your-domain.vercel.app/api/keystatic/github/oauth/callback
#
#    For preview deployments, you might also need:
#    - https://*.vercel.app/api/keystatic/github/oauth/callback
#
# 3. After creating the app:
#    - Copy the Client ID
#    - Click "Generate a new client secret" and copy it immediately (you won't see it again)
#
# 4. Add to Vercel:
#    - Go to your Vercel project → Settings → Environment Variables
#    - Add KEYSTATIC_GITHUB_CLIENT_ID and KEYSTATIC_GITHUB_CLIENT_SECRET
#    - IMPORTANT: Set for ALL environments (Production, Preview, Development)
#    - IMPORTANT: After adding variables, you MUST redeploy for them to take effect
#
# 5. Verify repository access:
#    - Make sure your GitHub account has write access to: Kapinoida/dcplaskett-portfolio-working
#    - If it's an organization, ensure the OAuth app is authorized for that org
